Defendant Casey V. Koeppel in court with attorney Eric Daniel Lowenberg.  Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1 and a no contest plea on Count #4.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.  Count #3 is dismissed by operation of law.   The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:  

6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT;
3 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT;
3 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION; 

*D/L REVOCATION: 36 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel on 6/22/16 (defendant to serve 20 days jail as penalty for non attendance of VIP)
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done. Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
*Perform 100 Hours of Community Service.

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation - to be forward to Waukesha Police Department);

FINE:  $1569.00 (apply cash bail and balance to to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE: $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME:  1 YEAR  NON WORKING HOURS w/Standard Release Conditions. (apply 1 day credit) Defendant remanded into custody and sentence to begin forthwith. 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given. 

Count #4:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:  

JAIL: 12 MONTHS (consecutive to count #1)

TERM OF PROBATION: 1 YEAR 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
See Count #1

DNA SURCHARGE: $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

COSTS: $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
